  "manufacturing": {
    "method": "fluorescein iodination",
    "description": "Resorcinol reacts with phthalic anhydride through condensation to form fluorescein. The fluorescein undergoes iodination to introduce four iodine atoms at positions 2, 4, 5, and 7, producing the bright cherry-red dye. It is then converted to the disodium salt (Erythrosin B) for water solubility."
  },
